0a%20new%2C%20jet-powered%20version%20of%20its%20Shahed%20loitering%20munitions%2C%20suspicions%20are%20growing%20that%20Russia%20is%20in%20possession%20of%20the%20explosive%20weapon%20%E2%80%94%20and%20may%20have%20already%20used%20a%20variant%20of%20it%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jet%20engine-powered%20Shahed-238%20is%20a%20significant%20upgrade%20in%20speed%20and%20altitude%20over%20the%20propeller-driven%20versions%20of%20these%20Iranian-made%20drones%20that%20Russia%20has%20used%20to%20attack%20Ukrainian%20cities%20for%20over%20a%20year.%20This%20new%20capability%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Russian%20military%20could%20create%20headaches%20for%20Kyiv's%20air%20defenses%20by%20reducing%20reaction%20time%2C%20putting%20additional%20pressure%20on%20already-strained%20systems%2C%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIran%20has%20built%20a%20vast%20arsenal%20of%20one-way%20attack%20drones%2C%20but%20perhaps%20the%20most%20well-known%20of%20these%20weapons%20is%20the%20Shahed-136%2C%20which%20have%20been%20employed%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-suicide-drones-terror-chaos-among-ukrainian-civilians-expert-officials-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20across%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.centcom.mil%2FMEDIA%2FNEWS-ARTICLES%2FNews-Article-View%2FArticle%2F3225713%2Fus-navy-analysis-confirms-iranian-link-to-drone-attack%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMiddle%20East%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20Shahed-136%20is%20often%20called%20a%20drone%2C%20it's%20technically%20a%20loitering%20munition%2C%20meaning%20it%20can%20lurk%20above%20a%20target%20before%20flying%20into%20it%20and%20detonating.%20It's%20a%20small%20system%20that's%20powered%20by%20a%20propeller%20and%20can%20carry%20an%20explosive%20payload%20of%20up%20to%20an%20estimated%20110%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmediacenter.org.ua%2Fnew-i