hman%20hunting%20animals%20and%20cooking%20meat%20to%20assuage%20their%20hunger.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20exchange%20has%20Hindu%20zealots%20up%20in%20arms.%20Because%20some%20delicate%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20Hindu%20vegetarian%20sensibilities%20have%20been%20injured%20by%20the%20mere%20idea%20that%20Rama%20could%20be%20spoken%20of%20as%20eating%20meat%2C%20and%20that%20too%20at%20the%20time%20when%20the%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Epranpratishtha%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(life%20establishment)%20ritual%20around%20the%20idol%20of%20Ram%20in%20the%20new%20temple%20at%20Ayodhya%20is%20about%20to%20take%20place.%20Matters%20are%20further%20complicated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20occurs%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20film%20depicting%20a%20friendship%20between%20a%20Hindu%20woman%20and%20a%20Muslim%20man.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fayodhya-rss-bjp-vhp-ram-temple%5C%22%3EFour%20Decades%20of%20Milking%20a%20Deity%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20not%20just%20the%20question%20of%20culinary%20blasphemy%2C%20but%20also%20the%20civilisational%20catastrophe%20of%20%E2%80%98love%20jihad%E2%80%99%20is%20invoked.%20Police%20complaints%20against%20the%20filmmakers%20have%20been%20filed%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Maharashtra.%20And%20now%20Netflix%2C%20the%20OTT%20platform%20where%20the%20film%20was%20being%20screened%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fannapoorani-netflix-zee5-hindutva%5C%22%3Ehas%20decided%20to%20remove%20the%20film%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Zee%20Studios%2C%20the%20producers%20of%20the%20film%2C%20have%20offered%20an%20%E2%80%98apology%E2%80%99%2C%20needlessly%2C%20for%20having%20%E2%80%98hurt%20Hindu%20sentiments%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20question%20is%20we%20need%20to%20ask%20is%3A%20Can%20Ram%2C%20Lakshman%20and%20Sita%20eat%20meat%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3ECan%20we%20even%20think%20such%20a%20thought%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApparently%20Valmiki%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20problem%20with%20entertaining%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20scene%20in%20the%20film%20(I%20have%20seen%20it)%20which%20has%20made%20the%20Hindutva%20hot-heads%20so%20hot%20and%20bothered%20features%20a%20conversation%20on%20a%20staircase%20between%20the%20Hindu%20female%20protagonist%20and%20her%20Muslim%20friend.%20He%20recites%20a%20passage%20from%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20Sanskrit%20to%20address%20her%20crisis%20about%20cooking%20meat.%20That%20verse%20is%20%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8C%20%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%E0%A5%A4%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%AD%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%E0%A5%A4%E0%A5%A42.52.102%E0%A5%A4%E0%A5%A4%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20find%20nothing%20per-se%20exceptional%20in%20a%20Muslim%20character%20citing%20a%20passage%20in%20Sanskrit%20from%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20best%20and%20most%20accessible%20translation%20from%20the%20Valmiki%20Ramayana%20into%20English%20has%20been%20done%20in%20my%20opinion%20by%20a%20Sanskrit%20scholar%2C%20Arshia%20Sattar%2C%20who%2C%20incidentally%2C%20happens%20to%20be%20a%20Muslim.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnyone%20even%20remotely%20familiar%20with%20the%20cultural%20histories%20of%20Kerala%2C%20Bengal%20or%20Rajasthan%20will%20know%20of%20the%20several%20versions%20of%20the%20Ramayana%20narrative%20that%20are%20an%20intrinsic%20part%20of%20the%20poetic%20and%20performative%20traditions%20cultivated%20within%20Muslim%20communities%20in%20these%20parts.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20modern%20retellings%2C%20in%20any%20Indian%20language%2C%20of%20a%20fragment%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E%20narrative%2C%20is%20Michael%20Madhusudan%20Dutt%E2%80%99s%20Bengali%20epic%20poem%2C%20%3Cem%3EMeghnadbadh%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ekabya%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Michael%20Madhusudan%20Dutt%20was%20Christian.%20As%20a%20Bengali%2C%20this%20work%20is%20formative%20for%20me.%20It%20typifies%20what%20the%20Bengali%20language%20is%20capable%20of.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20I%20too%20do%20not%20identify%20myself%20as%20a%20believer%2C%20I%20do%20read%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20a%20work%20of%20epic%20poetry.%20And%20I%20read%20it%20in%20Sanskrit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20passage%20in%20question%20is%20from%20the%20Ayodhya%20Kanda%2C%20chapter%2052%2C%20verse%20102.%20No%2C%20it%20is%20not%20from%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%98interpolated%E2%80%99%20sections%20of%20the%20Uttara-Kanda%2C%20as%20is%20being%20tom-tommed%20by%20some%20ignoramuses.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20passage%20describes%20a%20moment%2C%20early%20in%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20exile%2C%20when%2C%20having%20just%20left%20Ayodhya%20and%20crossed%20the%20river%20Sarayu%2C%20Ram%2C%20Lakshman%20and%20Sita%2C%20arrive%20in%20the%20territory%20of%20Vatsa%2C%20and%20tired%2C%20and%20hungry%2C%20decide%20to%20eat%20and%20spend%20the%20night%20under%20a%20tree.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20carefully%20at%20the%20passage.%20I%20offer%20a%20rough%20translation%20here%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFamished%20(%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%AD%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8C%20%2F%20bubhukshitau)%20they%20(Ram%20and%20Lakshman)%20there%2C%20then%2C%20(%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8C%20%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%20%2Ftau%20yatra)%20killed%2Fhunted%20(%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%20%2Fhatv%C4%81)%20four%20species%20of%C2%A0%20large%20animals%20(%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%20%2Fchaturo%20mah%C4%81mrig%C4%81n)%3A%20wild%20boar%20(%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B9%20%2Fvaraha%20)%2C%20white-footed%20antelope%20(%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%82%2Fmrishyam)%2C%20spotted%20deer%20(%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%82%20%2Fprishatam)%20and%20the%20great%20stag%20with%20black%20stripes%20(%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%20%2Fmaharurum)%3B%20ate%20(%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%20%2Fadaya)%20the%20meat%20(%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%82%2Fmedhyam)%20quickly%20(%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%82%3Ftvaritam)%20and%20rested%20underneath%20a%20tree%20(%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%20%2Fvasaya%E2%80%A6%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%20%2F%20yayaturvanaspatim)%20in%20the%20evening%20time%20(%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87%2Fk%C4%81l%C4%93).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnyone%20with%20any%20doubts%20about%20these%20words%20and%20their%20meanings%20can%20consult%20any%20standard%20Sanskrit%20lexicon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20fun%20to%20look%20for%20meat%20eating%20in%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20literally%20all%20over%20the%20text%20%E2%80%93%20but%C2%A0%20here%E2%80%99s%20another%20citation%20that%20is%20handy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%2034th%20and%2035th%20verses%20of%20the%2056th%20section%20(which%20describes%20Ram%2C%20Lakshman%E2%80%99s%20and%20Sita%E2%80%99s%20arrival%20at%20Chitrakuta%20during%20the%20early%20period%20of%20their%20forest%20exile)%20of%20the%20second%20book%20(%E2%80%98Ayodhya%20Kanda%E2%80%99)%20of%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E%20there%20is%20another%2C%20similar%20reference%20to%20meat%20eating.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%E2%80%99m%20offering%20the%20Sanskrit%20original%2C%20a%20Roman%20phonetic%20transliteration%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20Hindi%20and%20a%20rough%20English%20translation%20by%20me.%20The%20original%20text%20of%20this%20specific%20passage%2C%20and%20several%20translations%2C%20in%20different%20languages%2C%20are%20not%20difficult%20to%20find%20online.%20Those%20really%20interested%20might%20want%20to%20consult%20the%20text%20of%20the%20critical%2C%20annotated%2C%20edition%20of%20the%20Valmiki%20%3Cem%3ERamayan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(in%20seven%20volumes)%20first%20published%20in%201962%20by%20the%20Oriental%20Institute%20of%20the%20MS%20University%2C%20Baroda.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20here%20it%20is.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B9%20%E0%A4%AB%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%89%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%88%E0%A4%B9%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%