estinian%20women%20are%20giving%20birth%20daily%20amidst%20this%20chaos.%20People%20are%20facing%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20food%20insecurity%20ever%20recorded.%20Famine%20is%20around%20the%20corner.%20For%20children%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20past%2012%20weeks%20have%20been%20traumatic%3A%20No%20food.%20No%20water.%20No%20school.%20Nothing%20but%20the%20terrifying%20sounds%20of%20war%2C%20day%20in%20and%20day%20out.%20Gaza%20has%20simply%20become%20uninhabitable.%20Its%20people%20are%20witnessing%20daily%20threats%20to%20their%20very%20existence%20%E2%80%94%20while%20the%20world%20watches%20on.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20has%20heard%20of%20the%20horrific%20death%20toll%2C%20and%20of%20the%20more%20than%207%2C000%20Palestinian%20men%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cnwomen%20and%20children%20reported%20missing%2C%20presumed%20dead%20or%20dying%20slow%2C%20excruciating%20deaths%20trapped%3Cbr%3E%5Cnunder%20the%20rubble.%20Reports%20of%20field%20executions%2C%20and%20torture%20and%20ill-treatment%20are%20mounting%2C%20as%20are%20images%20of%20decomposing%20bodies%20of%20Palestinian%20men%2C%20women%20and%20children%2C%20left%20unburied%20where%20they%3Cbr%3E%5Cnwere%20killed%20%E2%80%94%20some%20being%20picked%20upon%20by%20animals.%20It%20is%20becoming%20ever%20clearer%20that%20huge%20swathes%20of%20Gaza%20%E2%80%94%20entire%20towns%2C%20villages%2C%20refugee%20camps%20%E2%80%94%20are%20being%20wiped%20from%20the%20map.%20As%20you%20have%3Cbr%3E%5Cnheard%2C%20but%20it%20bears%20repeating%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Food%20Programme%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5Bf%5Dour%20out%20of%20five%20people%20%5Bin%20the%20world%5D%2C%20in%20famine%20or%20a%20catastrophic%20type%20of%20hunger%2C%20are%20in%20Gaza%20right%20now%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20deaths%20from%20starvation%20and%20disease%20risk%20significantly%20outstripping%20deaths%20from%20bombings.%20The%20daily%20statistics%20stand%20as%20clear%20evidence%20of%20the%20urgency%20and%20of%20the%20irreparable%20prejudice%3A%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20current%20figures%2C%20on%20average%20Palestinians%20are%20being%20killed%20and%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20killed%20each%20day%2C%20many%20of%20them%20literally%20blown%20to%20pieces.%20They%20include%2048%20mothers%20each%20day%20%E2%80%94%20two%20every%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20209%20and%20over%20117%20children%20each%20day%2C%20leading%20UNICEF%20to%20call%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions%20a%20%E2%80%9Cwar%20on%20children%E2%80%9D.%20On%20current%20rates%2C%20which%20show%20no%20sign%20of%20abating%2C%20each%20day%2C%20over%20three%20medics%2C%20two%20teachers%2C%20more%20than%20one%20United%20Nations%20employee%20and%20more%20than%20one%20journalist%20will%20be%20killed%20%E2%80%94%20many%20while%20at%20work%2C%20or%20in%20what%20appear%20to%20be%20targeted%20attacks%20on%20their%20family%20homes%20or%20where%20they%20are%20sheltering.%20The%20risk%20of%20famine%20will%20increase%20each%20day.%20Each%20day%2C%20an%20average%20of%20629%20people%20will%20be%20wounded%2C%20some%20multiple%20times%20over%20as%20they%20move%20from%20place%20to%20place%2C%20desperately%20seeking%20sanctuary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20day%2C%20over%2010%20Palestinian%20children%20will%20have%20one%20or%20both%20legs%20amputated%2C%20many%20without%20anaesthetic.%20Each%20day%2C%20on%20current%20rates%2C%20an%20average%20of%203%2C900%20Palestinian%20homes%20will%20be%20damaged%20or%20destroyed.%20More%20mass%20graves%20will%20be%20dug.%20More%20cemeteries%20will%20be%20bulldozed%20and%20bombed%20and%20corpses%20violently%20exhumed%2C%20denying%20even%20the%20dead%20any%20dignity%20or%20peace.%20Each%20day%2C%20ambulances%2C%20hospitals%20and%20medics%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20attacked%20and%20killed.%20The%20first%20responders%20who%20have%20spent%20three%20months%20%E2%80%94%20without%20international%20assistance%20%E2%80%94%20trying%20to%20dig%20families%20out%20of%20the%20rubble%20with%20their%20bare%20hands%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20targeted%3B%20on%20current%20figures%20one%20will%20be%20killed%20almost%20every%20second%20day%2C%20sometimes%20in%20attacks%20launched%20against%20those%20attending%20the%20scene%20to%20rescue%20the%20wounded.%20Each%20day%20yet%20more%20desperate%20people%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20relocate%20from%20where%20they%20are%20sheltering%20or%20will%20be%20bombed%20in%20places%20where%20they%20had%20been%20told%20to%20evacuate%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEntire%20multi-generational%20families%20will%20be%20obliterated%3B%20and%20yet%20more%20Palestinian%20children%20will%20become%20%E2%80%9CWCNSF%E2%80%9D%3A%20%E2%80%9CWounded%20Child%20%E2%80%93%20No%20Surviving%20Family%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20the%20terrible%20new%20acronym%20borne%20out%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20genocidal%20assault%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20for%20provisional%20measures%20to%20prevent%20imminent%2C%20irreparable%20prejudice%20to%20the%20rights%20in%20issue%20in%20this%20case.%20There%20could%20not%20be%20a%20clearer%20or%20more%20compelling%20case.%20In%20the%20words%20of%20the%20Commissioner-General%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency%2C%20there%20must%20be%20%E2%80%9Can%20end%20to%20the%20decimation%20of%20Gaza%20and%20of%20its%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%E2%80%99s%20case%20law%20Criterion%20of%20urgency%2010.%20Turning%20to%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20case%20law%2C%20as%20the%20Court%20has%20recently%20reaffirmed%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5Bt%5Dhe%20condition%20of%20urgency%20is%20met%20when%20acts%20susceptible%20of%20causing%20irreparable%20prejudice%20can%20%E2%80%98occur%20at%20any%20moment%E2%80%99%20before%20the%20Court%20makes%20a%20final%20decision%20on%20the%20case%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20precisely%20the%20situation%20here.%20Any%20of%20those%20matters%20to%20which%20I%20have%20referred%20can%20and%20are%20occurring%20at%20any%20moment.%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20resolutions%20demanding%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20immediate%2C%20safe%2C%20unhindered%20delivery%20of%20humanitarian%20assistance%2C%20at%20scale%E2%80%9Dthroughout%20Gaza%20and%20%E2%80%9Cfull%2C%20rapid%2C%20safe%2C%20and%20unhindered%20humanitarian%20access%E2%80%9Dremain%20unimplemented.%20United%20Nations%20General%20Assembly%20resolutions%20calling%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20ceasefire%20have%20been%20ignored.%20The%20situation%20could%20not%20be%20more%20urgent.%20Since%20these%20proceedings%20were%20initiated%20on%2029%20December%202023%20alone%2C%20an%20estimated%20over%201%2C703%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%2C%20and%20over%203%2C252%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIrreparable%20prejudice%3A%20serious%20risks%20to%20human%20life%20and%20other%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20to%20the%20criterion%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%2C%20for%20decades%20now%2C%20the%20Court%20has%20repeatedly%20found%20it%20to%20be%20satisfied%20in%20situations%20where%20serious%20risks%20arise%20to%20human%20life%20or%20to%20other%20fundamental%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20cases%20of%20Georgia%20v.%20Russia%2C%20and%20Armenia%20v.%20Azerbaijan%2C%20the%20Court%20ordered%20provisional%20measures%20having%20found%20a%20serious%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%20where%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20had%20been%20forced%20from%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20ordering%20provisional%20measures%20in%20the%20latter%20case%2C%20the%20Court%20noted%20the%20context%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20long-standing%20exposure%20of%20the%20population%20.%20.%20.%20to%20a%20situation%20of%20vulnerability%E2%80%9D%20including%20%E2%80%9Chindrances%20to%20the%20importation%20.%20.%20.%20of%20essential%20goods%2C%20causing%20shortages%20of%20food%2C%20medicine%2C%20and%20other%20life-saving%20medical%20supplies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Gaza%2C%20as%20you%20have%20heard%2C%20nearly%20two%20million%20people%20%E2%80%94%20over%2085%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20population%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20repeatedly%20forced%20to%20flee%20their%20homes%20and%20shelters%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20once%20or%20twice%20but%20some%20three%2C%20four%20or%20more%20times%20over%20%E2%80%94%20into%20shrinking%20slivers%20of%20land%2C%20where%20they%20continue%20to%20be%20bombed%20and%20killed.%20This%20is%20a%20population%20that%20Israel%20had%20already%20made%20vulnerable%20through%2016%20years%20of%20military%20blockade%20and%20crippling%20%E2%80%9Cde-development%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Chindrances%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20import%20of%20food%20and%20essential%20items%20have%20brought%20Gaza%20%E2%80%9Cto%20the%20brink%20of%20famine%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20mothers%2C%20fathers%2C%20grandparents%20%E2%80%94%20regularly%20foregoing%20food%20for%20the%20day%20so%20that%20children%20can%20eat%20at%20least%20something.%20Medicine%20shortages%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20medical%20treatment%2C%20clean%20water%20and%20electricity%2C%20are%20so%20great%20that%20large%20numbers%20of%20Palestinians%20are%20dying%20or%20are%20at%20imminent%20risk%20of%20dying%20preventable%20deaths%2C%20cancer%20and%20other%20services%20have%20long%20shut%20down%2C%20women%20are%20undergoing%20caesarean%20sections%20without%20anaesthetic%2C%20in%20barely%20functioning%20hospitals%20described%20as%20scenes%20from%20a%20%E2%80%9Chorror%20movie%E2%80%9D.%20with%20many%20undergoing%20otherwise%20unnecessary%20hysterectomies%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20save%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Canada%20and%20the%20Netherlands%20v.%20Syria%20torture%20case%2C%20the%20Court%20made%20clear%20that%20%E2%80%9Cindividuals%20subject%20to%20torture%20and%20other%20acts%20of%20cruel%2C%20inhuman%20or%20degrading%20treatment%20or%20punishment%20.%20.%20.%20are%20at%20serious%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%E2%80%9D.%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20are%20also%20at%20risk%20of%20such%20irreparable%20prejudice%2C%20with%20videos%20of%20Palestinian%20boys%20and%20men%2C%20rounded%20up%20and%20stripped%20and%20degraded%2C%20broadcast%20to%20the%20world%2C%20alongside%20footage%20of%20serious%20bodily%20harm%2C%20and%20accounts%20of%20serious%20mental%20harm%20and%20humiliation.%20In%20Qatar%20v.%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20the%20Court%20considered%20provisional%20measures%20to%20be%20justified%20having%20regard%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%20deriving%20from%20factors%20such%20as%3A%20people%20being%20forced%20to%20leave%20their%20places%20of%20residence%20without%20the%20possibility%20of%20return%3B%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpsychological%20distress%E2%80%9D%20of%20%E2%80%9Ctemporary%20or%20potentially%20ongoing%20separation%20from%20their%20families%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20harm%20associated%20with%20students%20being%20%E2%80%9Cprevented%20from%20taking%20their%20exams%E2%80%9D.%20If%20provisional%20measures%20were%20justified%20there%2C%20how%20could%20they%20not%20be%20in%20Gaza%2C%20where%20countless%20families%20have%20been%20separated%20%E2%80%94%20with%20some%20family%20members%20evacuating%20under%20Israeli%20military%20orders%20and%20others%20staying%20behind%20at%20extreme%20risk%20to%20care%20for%20the%20wounded%2C%20infirm%20and%20the%20elderly%3B%20where%20husbands%2C%20fathers%20and%20sons%20are%20being%20rounded%20up%20and%20separated%20from%20their%20families%2C%20taken%20to%20unknown%20locations%20for%20indeterminate%20periods%20of%20time.%20In%20the%20Qatar%20case%2C%20the%20Court%20issued%20a%20provisional%20measures%20Order%20where%20harm%20to%20approximately%20150%20students%20was%20in%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Gaza%2C%20625%2C000%20school%20children%20have%20not%20attended%20school%20for%20three%20months%2C%20with%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20%E2%80%9C%5Be%5Dxpressing%20deep%20concern%20that%20the%20disruption%20of%20access%20to%20education%20has%20a%20dramatic%20impact%20on%20children%2C%20and%20that%20conflict%20has%20lifelong%20effects%20on%20their%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%E2%80%9D.%20Almost%2090%2C000%20Palestinian%20university%20students%20cannot%20attend%20university%20in%20Gaza.%20Over%2060%20per%20cent%20of%20schools%2C%20almost%20all%20universities%20and%20countless%20bookshops%20and%20libraries%20have%20been%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20teachers%20and%20academics%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20including%20deans%20of%20universities%20and%20leading%20Palestinian%20scholars%2C%20obliterating%20the%20very%20prospects%20for%20the%20future%20education%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20children%20and%20young%20people.%20Provisional%20measures%20and%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20Court%20has%20found%20provisional%20measures%20to%20be%20justified%20in%20all%20three%20cases%20where%20they%20were%20previously%20sought%20in%20relation%20to%20violations%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%20It%20did%20so%20in%20Bosnia%20v.%20Serbia%20in%201993%2C%20finding%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20evidence%20that%20was%20certainly%20no%20more%20compelling%20than%20that%20presently%20before%20the%20Court%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it%20was%20sufficient%20to%20determine%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20grave%20risk%20of%20acts%20of%20genocide%20being%20committed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20found%20provisional%20measures%20to%20be%20justified%20in%20The%20Gambia%20v.%20Myanmar%20case%2C%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%20to%20the%20Rohingya%2C%20%E2%80%9Csubjected%20to%20.%20.%20.%20mass%20killings%20.%20.%20.%20as%20well%20as%20beatings%2C%20the%20destruction%20of%20villages%20and%20homes%2C%20denial%20of%20access%20to%20food%2C%20shelter%20and%20other%20essentials%20of%20life.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20in%20indicating%20provisional%20measures%20in%20Ukraine%20v.%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20the%20Court%20considered%20that%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20military%20activities%20had%20%E2%80%9Cresulted%20in%20numerous%20civilian%20deaths%20and%20injuries%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccaused%20significant%20material%20damage%2C%20including%20the%20destruction%20of%20buildings%20and%20infrastructure%E2%80%9D%2C%20giving%20rise%20to%20a%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice.%20The%20Court%20had%20regard%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9C%5Ba%5Dttacks%20are%20ongoing%20and%20are%20creating%20increasingly%20difficult%20living%20conditions%20for%20the%20civilian%20population%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20it%20considered%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20vulnerable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20also%20considered%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9C%5Bm%5Dany%20persons%20have%20no%20access%20to%20the%20most%20basic%20foodstuffs%2C%20potable%20water%2C%20electricity%2C%20essential%20medicines%20or%20heating%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20many%20were%20attempting%20to%20flee%20%E2%80%9Cunder%20extremely%20insecure%20conditions%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20occurring%20in%20Gaza%20on%20a%20much%20more%20intensive%20scale%2C%20to%20a%20besieged%2C%20trapped%2C%20terrified%20population%20that%20has%20nowhere%20safe%20to%20go.%20Provisional%20measures%20in%20situations%20of%20armed%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELest%20the%20contrary%20be%20suggested%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20from%20Ukraine%20v.%20Russian%20Federation%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20urgent%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20harm%20arises%20in%20a%20situation%20of%20armed%20conflict%20does%20not%20undermine%20much%20less%20preclude%20a%20request%20for%20provisional%20measures.%20That%20is%20also%20clear%20from%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20other%20Judgments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Armed%20Activities%20on%20the%20Territory%20of%20the%20Congo%20(Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo%20v.%20Uganda)264%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20Court%20ordered%20provisional%20measures%20based%20on%20its%20finding%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20persons%2C%20assets%20and%20resources%20present%20on%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20Congo%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20area%20of%20conflict%2C%20remain%20extremely%20vulnerable%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20serious%20risk%20that%20the%20rights%20at%20issue%20in%20this%20case%20.%20.%20.%20may%20suffer%20irreparable%20prejudice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20Costa%20Rica%20v.%20Nicaragua%2C%20the%20Court%20indicated%20provisional%20measures%20in%20part%20on%20the%20basis%20that%20the%20presence%20of%20troops%20in%20the%20disputed%20territory%20gave%20%E2%80%9Crise%20to%20a%20real%20and%20present%20risk%20of%20incidents%20liable%20to%20cause%20irremediable%20harm%20in%20the%20form%20of%20bodily%20injury%20or%20death%E2%80%9D.%20In%20relation%20to%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20Court%20recalled%20in%20The%20Gambia%20v.%20Myanmar%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9CStates%20parties%20expressly%20confirmed%20their%20willingness%20to%20consider%20genocide%20as%20a%20crime%20under%20international%20law%20which%20they%20must%20prevent%20and%20punish%20independently%20of%20the%20context%20%E2%80%98of%20peace%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98of%20war%E2%80%99%20in%20which%20it%20takes%20place%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Guyana%20v.%20Venezuela%2C%20the%20Court%20considered%20that%20the%20serious%20risk%20of%20Venezuela%20%E2%80%9Cacquiring%20and%20exercising%20control%20and%20administration%20of%20the%20territory%20in%20dispute%E2%80%9D%20gave%20rise%20to%20a%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%20to%20the%20rights%20asserted%20in%20the%20case.%20Similar%20factors%20are%20in%20issue%20here%2C%20having%20regard%20to%20the%20territorial%20ambitions%20and%20settlement%20plans%20for%20Gaza%20being%20raised%20by%20members%20of%20the%20Israeli%20Government%2C%20and%20the%20relationship%20of%20those%20factors%20to%20the%20very%20survival%20of%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20as%20such.%20Provisional%20measures%20and%20mitigation%20of%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20any%20scaling%20up%20by%20Israel%20of%20access%20of%20humanitarian%20relief%20to%20Gaza%20in%20response%20to%20these%20proceedings%20or%20otherwise%20would%20be%20no%20answer%20to%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20request%20for%20provisional%20measures.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Iran%20v.%20United%20States%2C%20the%20Court%20found%20a%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20harm%20from%20the%20exposure%20of%20individuals%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdanger%20to%20health%20and%20life%E2%80%9Dcaused%20by%20restrictions%20placed%20on%20%E2%80%9Cmedicines%20and%20medical%20devices%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cfoodstuffs%E2%80%9D%20and%20other%20%E2%80%9Cgoods%20required%20for%20humanitarian%20needs%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20notwithstanding%20the%20assurances%20offered%20by%20the%20United%20States%20for%20it%20to%20expedite%20the%20consideration%20of%20humanitarian%20issues%3B%20and%20notwithstanding%20the%20fact%20that%20essentials%20were%20in%20any%20event%20exempt%20from%20the%20United%20States%20sanctions.%20The%20Court%20considered%20that%20the%20assurances%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20adequate%20to%20address%20fully%20the%20humanitarian%20and%20safety%20concerns%20raised%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20remain%5Bed%5D%20a%20risk%20that%20measures%20adopted%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20United%20States%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20entail%20irreparable%20consequences%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Armenia%20v.%20Azerbaijan%2C%20unilateral%20undertakings%20to%20alleviate%20restrictions%20alongside%20the%20full%20resumption%20of%20humanitarian%20and%20commercial%20deliveries%20did%20not%20defeat%20a%20request%20for%20the%20indication%20of%20provisional%20measures.%20The%20Court%20was%20clear%20that%20while%20contributing%20%E2%80%9Ctowards%20mitigating%20the%20imminent%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%20resulting%20from%E2%80%9D%20the%20military%20operation%2C%20those%20developments%20did%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20remove%20the%20risk%20entirely%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20in%20Georgia%20v.%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20the%20Court%20made%20clear%20that%20it%20considers%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20risk%E2%80%9D%20to%20subsist%20where%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20situation%20.%20.%20.%20is%20unstable%20and%20could%20rapidly%20change%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Court%20considered%20that%20%E2%80%9Cgiven%20the%20ongoing%20tension%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20overall%20settlement%20to%20the%20conflict%20in%20this%20region%20.%20.%20.%20populations%20also%20remain%20vulnerable%E2%80%9D.%20Israel%20continues%20to%20deny%20that%20it%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20humanitarian%20crisis%20it%20has%20created%2C%20even%20as%20Gaza%20starves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-south-africa-genocidal-acts-icj%5C%22%3EHarm%2C%20Calculation%2C%20Reproductive%20Violence%3A%20Why%20South%20Africa%20Feels%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Conduct%20in%20Gaza%20Is%20Genocide%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aid%20it%20has%20belatedly%20begun%20to%20allow%20in%20is%20wholly%20inadequate%20and%20does%20not%20come%20anywhere%20close%20to%20the%20average%20500%20trucks%20being%20permitted%20daily%20before%20October%202023%2C%20even%20under%20the%20blockade.%20Any%20unilateral%20undertakings%20Israel%20might%20seek%20to%20give%20about%20future%20aid%20would%20not%20remove%20the%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20prejudice%2C%20not%20least%20considering%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20past%20and%20current%20conduct%20towards%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20including%20the%2016%20years%20of%20brutal%20siege%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20event%2C%20as%20the%20United%20Nations%20Secretary-General%20has%20made%20absolutely%20clear%2C%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20mistake%E2%80%9D%20to%20measure%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20effectiveness%20of%20the%20humanitarian%20operation%20in%20Gaza%20based%20on%20the%20number%20of%20trucks%E2%80%9D%20allowed%20in.%20As%20he%20stressed%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5Bt%5Dhe%20real%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20way%20Israel%20is%20conducting%20this%20offensive%E2%80%9D%20means%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20conditions%20for%20the%20effective%20delivery%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%20no%20longer%20exist%E2%80%9D.%20That%20would%20require%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%2C%20staff%20who%20can%20work%20in%20safety%2C%20logistical%20capacity%2C%20and%20the%20resumption%20of%20commercial%20activity.%20It%20requires%20electricity%20and%20steady%20communications.%20All%20of%20these%20remain%20absent%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20only%20shortly%20after%20Israel%20opened%20the%20Kerem%20Shalom%20crossing%20to%20goods%20in%20late%20December%202023%2C%20it%20was%20struck%20in%20a%20drone%20attack%2C%20killing%20five%20Palestinians%20and%20leading%20to%20another%20temporary%20closure.%20Nowhere%20and%20nobody%20is%20safe.%20As%20the%20United%20Nations%20Secretary-General%20and%20all%20its%20chiefs%20have%20made%20clear%2C%20without%20a%20halt%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20operations%2C%20crossings%2C%20aid%20convoys%20and%20humanitarian%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20like%20everyone%20and%20everything%20else%20in%20Gaza%20%E2%80%94%20remain%20at%20imminent%20risk%20of%20further%20irreparable%20prejudice.%20An%20unprecedented%20148%20United%20Nations%20staff%20have%20been%20killed%20to%20date.%20Without%20a%20halt%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20activity%20in%20Gaza%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20end%20to%20the%20extreme%20situation%20facing%20Palestinian%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProvisional%20measures%20and%20Gaza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMadam%20President%2C%20Members%20of%20the%20Court%2C%20if%20the%20indication%20of%20provisional%20measures%20was%20justified%20on%20the%20facts%20in%20those%20cases%20I%20have%20cited%2C%20how%20could%20it%20not%20be%20here%2C%20in%20a%20situation%20of%20much%20greater%20severity%2C%20where%20the%20imminent%20risk%20of%20irreparable%20harm%20is%20so%20much%20greater%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20could%20they%20not%20be%20justified%20in%20a%20situation%20that%20humanitarian%20veterans%20from%20crises%20spanning%20as%20far%20back%20as%20the%20killing%20fields%20of%20Cambodia%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%9Cpeople%20who%20%5Bin%20the%20words%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Secretary-General%5D%20have%20seen%20everything%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20say%20it%20is%20so%20utterly%20%E2%80%9Cunprecedented%E2%80%9D%20that%20they%20are%20%E2%80%9Cout%20of%20words%20to%20describe%E2%80%9D%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20a%20complete%20departure%20from%20the%20long%20and%20established%20line%20of%20jurisprudence%20that%20this%20Court%20has%20firmly%20established%20%E2%80%94%20and%20recently%20reconfirmed%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20Court%20not%20to%20order%20provisional%20measures%20in%20this%20case.%20The%20imminent%20risk%20of%20death%2C%20harm%20and%20destruction%20that%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20face%20today%2C%20and%20that%20they%20risk%20every%20day%20during%20the%20pendency%20of%20these%20proceedings%2C%20on%20any%20view%20justifies%20%E2%80%94%20indeed%20compels%20%E2%80%94%20the%20indication%20of%20provisional%20measures.%20Some%20might%20say%20that%20the%20very%20reputation%20of%20international%20law%20%E2%80%94%20its%20ability%20and%20willingness%20to%20bind%20and%20to%20protect%20all%20peoples%20equally%20%E2%80%94%20hangs%20in%20the%20balance.%20Elementary%20principles%20of%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%20is%20about%20much%20more%20than%20legal%20precedent.%20It%20is%20also%20fundamentally%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconfirm%5Bation%5D%20and%20endorse%5Bment%20of%5D%20elementary%20principles%20of%20morality%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-south-africa-genocidal-intent-gaza-icj%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Repetition%20Says%20a%20Lot%20About%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Genocidal%20Intent%20in%20Gaza%E2%80%99%3A%20South%20Africa%20at%20ICJ%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20recalled%20the%201946%20General%20Assembly%20resolution%20on%20the%20crime%20of%20genocide%2C%20which%20made%20clear%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGenocide%20is%20a%20denial%20of%20the%20right%20of%20existence%20of%20entire%20human%20groups%2C%20as%20homicide%20is%20the%20denial%20of%20the%20right%20to%20live%20of%20individual%20human%20beings%3B%20such%20denial%20of%20the%20right%20of%20existence%20shocks%20the%20conscience%20of%20mankind%2C%20results%20in%20great%20losses%20to%20humanity%20in%20the%20form%20of%20cultural%20and%20other%20contributions%20represented%20by%20these%20human%20groups%2C%20and%20is%20contrary%20to%20moral%20law%20and%20to%20the%20spirit%20and%20aims%20of%20the%20United%20Nations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotwithstanding%20the%20Genocide%20Convention%E2%80%99s%20recognition%20of%20the%20need%20to%20rid%20the%20world%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Codious%20scourge%E2%80%9D%20of%20genocide%2C%20the%20international%20community%20has%20repeatedly%20failed.%20It%20%E2%80%9Cfailed%E2%80%9D%20the%20people%20of%20Rwanda.%20It%20had%20failed%20the%20Bosnian%20people%20and%20the%20Rohingya%2C%20prompting%20this%20Court%20to%20take%20action.%20It%20failed%20again%20by%20ignoring%20the%20early%20warnings%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20risk%20of%20genocide%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20people%E2%80%9D%20sounded%20by%20international%20experts%20since%2019%20October%20of%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20international%20community%20continues%20to%20fail%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20despite%20the%20overt%20dehumanizing%20genocidal%20rhetoric%20by%20Israeli%20governmental%20and%20military%20officials%2C%20matched%20by%20the%20Israeli%20army%E2%80%99s%20actions%20on%20the%20ground%3B%20despite%20the%20horror%20of%20the%20genocide%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20being%20livestreamed%20from%20Gaza%20to%20our%20mobile%20phones%2C%20computers%20and%20television%20screens%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20genocide%20in%20history%20where%20its%20victims%20are%20broadcasting%20their%20own%20destruction%20in%20real%20time%20in%20the%20desperate%20%E2%80%94%20so%20far%20vain%20%E2%80%94%20hope%20that%20the%20world%20might%20do%20something.%20Gaza%20represents%20nothing%20short%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmoral%20failure%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20described%20by%20the%20usually%20circumspect%20International%20Committee%20of%20the%20Red%20Cross.%20As%20underscored%20by%20United%20Nations%20chiefs%2C%20that%20failure%20has%20%E2%80%9Crepercussions%20not%20just%20for%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza%20.%20.%20.%20but%20for%20the%20generations%20to%20come%20who%20will%20never%20forget%20these%20%5Bover%5D%2090%20days%20of%20hell%20and%20of%20assaults%20on%20the%20most%20basic%20precepts%20of%20humanity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20stated%20by%20a%20United%20Nations%20spokesperson%20in%20Gaza%20last%20week%2C%20at%20the%20site%20of%20a%20hospital%20clearly%20marked%20with%20the%20symbol%20of%20the%20Red%20Crescent%2C%20where%20five%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20five-day-old%20baby%20%E2%80%94%20had%20just%20been%20killed%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20world%20should%20be%20absolutely%20horrified.%20The%20world%20should%20be%20absolutely%20outraged%20.%20.%20.%20There%20is%20no%20safe%20space%20in%20Gaza%20and%20the%20world%20should%20be%20ashamed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMadam%20President%2C%20Members%20of%20the%20Court%2C%20in%20conclusion%20I%20share%20with%20you%20two%20photographs.%20The%20first%20is%20of%20a%20whiteboard%20at%20a%20hospital%20%E2%80%94%20in%20northern%20Gaza%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20many%20Palestinian%20hospitals%20targeted%2C%20besieged%20and%20bombed%20by%20Israel%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20past%20three%20brutal%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20whiteboard%20is%20wiped%20clean%20of%20no%20longer%20possible%20surgical%20cases%2C%20leaving%20only%20a%20hand-written%20message%20by%20a%20M%C3%A9decins%20Sans%20Fronti%C3%A8res%20doctor%20which%20reads%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20did%20what%20we%20could.%20Remember%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20photograph%20is%20of%20the%20same%20whiteboard%2C%20after%20an%20Israeli%20strike%20on%20the%20hospital%20on%2021%20November%20that%20killed%20the%20author%20of%20the%20message%2C%20Dr%20Mahmoud%20Abu%20Nujaila%2C%20along%20with%20two%20of%20his%20colleagues.%20Just%20over%20a%20month%20later%2C%20in%20a%20powerful%20sermon%2C%20delivered%20from%20a%20church%20in%20Bethlehem%20on%20Christmas%20Day%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20day%20Israel%20had%20killed%20250%20Palestinians%2C%20including%20at%20least%2086%20people%2C%20many%20from%20the%20same%20family%2C%20massacred%20in%20a%20single%20strike%20on%20Maghazi%20refugee%20camp%20%E2%80%94%20Palestinian%20Pastor%20Munther%20Isaac%20addressed%20his%20congregation%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CGaza%20as%20we%20know%20it%20no%20longer%20exists.%20This%20is%20an%20annihilation.%20This%20is%20a%20genocide.%20We%20will%20rise.%20We%20will%20stand%20up%20again%20from%20the%20midst%20of%20destruction%2C%20as%20we%20have%20always%20done%20as%20Palestinians%2C%20although%20this%20is%20by%20far%20maybe%20the%20biggest%20blow%20we%20have%20received.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20apologies%20will%20be%20accepted%20after%20the%20genocide%20.%20.%20.%20What%20has%20been%20done%20has%20been%20done.%20I%20want%20you%20to%20look%20at%20the%20mirror%20and%20ask%2C%20%E2%80%98where%20was%20I%20when%20Gaza%20was%20going%20through%20a%20genocide%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%20is%20here%20before%20this%20Court%2C%20in%20the%20Peace%20Palace.%20It%20has%20done%20what%20it%20could.%20It%20is%20doing%20what%20it%20can%2C%20by%20initiating%20these%20proceedings%2C%20by%20seeking%20interim%20measures%20against%20itself%20as%20well%20as%20a