%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDebt%20commitments%20decreased%20to%20%24625.91%20million%20in%20December%202023%2C%20down%20from%20%241.15%20billion%20a%20year%20ago.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20higher%20than%20%24190.05%20million%20in%20November%202023.%20Guarantees%20for%20overseas%20units%20declined%20to%20%24978.19%20million%20in%20December%202023%20from%20%241.58%20billion%20in%20December%202022.%20They%20were%20down%20substantially%20compared%20to%20%242.72%20billion%20in%20November%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20reported%2C%20citing%20RBI%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20OFDI%20fell%20by%2012.14%25%20sequentially%20to%20%241.88%20billion%2C%20compared%20to%20over%20%242.14%20billion%20in%20September.%20According%20to%20RBI%20data%2C%20this%20was%20also%20a%20decrease%20from%20the%20over%20%242.66%20billion%20recorded%20in%20October%202022%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Findia-s-outward-foreign-direct-investment-dips-to-1-88-bn-in-october-123111300624_1.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20attributed%20the%20decline%20to%20a%20slowdown%20in%20economic%20and%20business%20activities%2C%20especially%20in%20developed%20markets%2C%20that%20has%20impacted%20direct%20investment%20flows%2C%20both%20inbound%20and%20outbound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20investments%20in%20OFDI%20take%20the%20form%20of%20subsidiaries%20or%20stakes%20in%20foreign%20companies.%20Bankers%20attribute%20the%20decline%20in%20opportunities%20to%20a%20slowdown%20in%20developed%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705059913000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F01171239%2Findian-rupee-money-cash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findias-outward-foreign-direct-investment-sharply-declines-to-2-25-billion-in-december-rbi-data%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OFDI%20is%20a%20business%20strategy%20in%20which%20a%20domestic%20firm%20expands%20its%20operations%20to%20a%20foreign%20country.%20According%20to%20'Business%20Standard'%2C%20they%20were%20also%20down%20from%20%244%20billion%20in%20November%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findias-outward-foreign-direct-investment-sharply-declines-to-2-25-billion-in-december-rbi-data%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Short%20History%20of%20the%20Australian%20Open%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F01%2F3923108456_185726e5a8_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20relatively%20humble%20beginnings%2C%20the%20Australian%20Open%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20centrepiece%20in%20both%20the%20global%20tennis%20and%20Australian%20sporting%20calendar.%20With%20the%202024%20tournament%20approaching%2C%20the%20event%20is%20now%20a%20centurion%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20101%20years%20since%20it%20became%20a%20designated%20grand%20slam%2C%20and%20119%20years%20since%20the%20very%20first%20edition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Australian%20Open%20is%20now%20firmly%20known%20as%20a%20Melbourne%20event%2C%20the%20tournament%20used%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grandslamhistory.com%2Fvenues%2Fgrand-slam%2Faustralian-open%5C%22%3Erotate%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20Australasia%20until%201972.%20Between%201905%20and%201971%2C%20it%20was%20most%20often%20hosted%20in%20Sydney%20(17%20times)%2C%20Melbourne%20(16)%2C%20Adelaide%20(15)%2C%20Brisbane%20(seven)%2C%20Perth%20(three)%2C%20and%20across%20the%20ditch%20in%20New%20Zealand%20(once%20in%20Christchurch%2C%20once%20in%20Hastings).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20early%20tournaments%20were%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20economic%20enterprise%20of%20the%20modern%20grand%20slam%3B%20the%201909%20edition%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20was%20held%20in%20the%20Perth%20Zoo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20after%20the%20International%20Lawn%20Tennis%20Federation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fds.amu.edu.et%2Fxmlui%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F6821%2FSport%2520Histories.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%26isAllowed%3Dy%23page%3D113%5C%22%3Edesignated%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Australian%20Open%20as%20one%20of%20the%20four%20grand%20slam%20tournaments%20in%201923%2C%20it%20lagged%20behind%20the%20others%20for%20quite%20some%20time.%20This%20was%20mainly%20due%20to%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20remoteness%2C%20the%20inconvenient%20timing%20of%20the%20tournament%20in%20December%20or%20January%2C%20the%20comparatively%20poor%20facilities%20and%20the%20low%20prize%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20tournament%20did%20not%20really%20flourish%20until%20the%201980s%20%E2%80%93%20well%20into%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Folympics.com%2Fen%2Fnews%2Ftennis-australian-open-stats-records-grand-slam%5C%22%3Eopen%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20professional%20tennis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growth%20of%20the%20Australian%20Open%20since%20the%201980s%20has%20occurred%20in%20parallel%20to%20the%20development%20of%20Melbourne%20as%20a%20cosmopolitan%20city.%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20deindustrialisation%20and%20financial%20deregulation%20in%20the%20early%201970s%20saw%20Sydney%20rise%20as%20the%20commercial%20capital%20of%20the%20country%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09523367.2012.746816%5C%22%3EMelbourne%20languished%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Melbourne%20turned%20to%20sport%20and%20culture%20as%20a%20form%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09523367.2012.746816%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20salvation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20moving%20away%20from%20manufacturing%20and%20towards%20tourism%2C%20leisure%20and%20spectacle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20resulted%20in%20significant%20infrastructure%20investment%2C%20including%20new%20grandstand%20capacity%20at%20Flemington%20racecourse%20and%20the%20installation%20of%20lights%20at%20the%20Melbourne%20Cricket%20Ground.%20Perhaps%20most%20significant%20was%20the%20building%20of%20Melbourne%20Park%20as%20a%20permanent%20facility%20for%20the%20Australian%20Open%20in%201988.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F09523367.2012.746816%5C%22%3Econtroversy%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20the%20necessary%20rezoning%20of%20public%20lands%20to%20create%20Melbourne%20Park%2C%20the%20relocation%20from%20the%20grass%20courts%20of%20Kooyong%20tennis%20club%20was%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.informit.org%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.3316%2FINFORMIT.143058285756777%5C%22%3Eimmediate%20success%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Total%20attendance%20increased%20from%20140%2C000%20to%20266%2C436%20in%20the%20first%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tournament%20has%20progressed%20by%20leaps%20and%20bounds%20since%20then.%20The%202023%20tournament%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fausopen.com%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Frecord-breaking-tournament-ao-2023-numbers%5C%22%3Ebroke%20attendance%20records%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20839%2C192%20people%20coming%20through%20the%20gates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBy%20the%20numbers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20Australian%20Open%20is%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20the%20Australian%20economy%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20mammoth%20operational%20undertaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tennis.com.au%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FAO-2023-By-the-Numbers-v3.pdf%5C%22%3E2023%20tournament%3C%2Fa%3E%20featured%20a%20total%20of%20817%20players%20from%2068%20nations%20and%20was%20reported%20on%20by%20more%20than%20800%20journalists%20and%20photographers%20from%2052%20nations.%20Incredibly%2C%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20staff%20from%20Tennis%20Australia%2C%20Melbourne%20%26amp%3B%20Olympic%20Parks%20and%20other%20related%20agencies%20helped%20stage%20the%20tournament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEconomically%2C%20over%20six%20million%20people%20have%20attended%20the%20Australian%20Open%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20contributing%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fausopen.com%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Fao-delivers-huge-economic-benefits-record-broadcast-numbers%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20A%242.71%20billion%20(US%241.76%20billion)%20to%20the%20Victorian%20state%20economy.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fausopen.com%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Fao-2020-delivers-record-benefits-victoria%5C%22%3EIn%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20last%20tournament%20before%20COVID%2C%20visitors%20booked%20574%2C970%20hotel%20night%20stays%20and%20spent%20on%20average%20A%24209%20per%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inherent%20cultural%20value%20of%20the%20Australian%20Open%20is%20apparent%20in%20annual%20surveying%20of%20local%20sentiment%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fausopen.com%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Fao-delivers-huge-economic-benefits-record-broadcast-numbers%5C%22%3E99%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Victorians%20agreeing%20in%202022%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20important%20for%20Victoria%20to%20host%20the%20Australian%20Open%20each%20year%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrong%20local%20support%20is%20important%20given%20the%20Victorian%20government%20invested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsport.vic.gov.au%2Four-work%2Finfrastructure%2Fmajor-infrastructure-projects%2FMelbourne-Park-redevelopment%5C%22%3EA%24972%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20(US%24629%20million)%20of%20taxpayer%20funds%20to%20redevelop%20Melbourne%20Park%20between%202010%20and%202019%20to%20secure%20the%20Australian%20Open%20hosting%20rights%20through%202046.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFuture%20challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20length%20of%20this%20deal%20is%20significant%2C%20given%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20other%20nations%20have%20become%20increasingly%20aggressive%20in%20attempting%20to%20rebrand%20themselves%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%